  "suggestion": "[information-theory+evaluation-theory+psychometrics] IMPLEMENT NOW — Real Fitness Function via Semantic Matching. The current fitness is always 1.0 (confidence is always > 0, so `active/total` is trivially 1.0). This means evolution has no gradient — the model cannot improve measurably. Fix: compare model output fields against benchmark `expected` fields. Score each benchmark: +1 if `emotion` matches `emotionChange` (case-insensitive substring), +1 if `behavior` matches expected `behavior` substring, +1 if any `mustInclude` term appears in rootCause+process+behavior, -1 if any `mustNotInclude` term appears. Normalize to 0–1 per benchmark, average across all. This single change unlocks real evolution. TypeScript implementation: iterate benchmarks, call predict(), string-match against expected, return mean score. — Math: fitness = mean_i(score_i); score_i = (emotionMatch + behaviorMatch + mustIncludeHits - mustNotIncludeHits) / maxPossible; [cognitive-psychology+Festinger-dissonance-theory+Bayesian-belief-updating] Belief-Dissonance Engine — Beliefs as Attractors. The model ignores person.beliefs entirely, but beliefs drive confirmation bias, motivated reasoning, sunk cost, and most cognitive-bias benchmarks. Model: each belief is a string that has a valence toward a domain (positive/negative). Stimulus description is matched against beliefs via keyword overlap. Dissonance = |stimulus_implied_valence - belief_valence|. High dissonance → belief-protection behavior (selective attention, dismiss contradicting info) + emotion 'cognitive dissonance'. Low dissonance + confirming → 'satisfied' + behavior 'assimilate/share'. This replaces the generic PE calculation for the cognitive-bias domain. Two mechanisms run in parallel: need-PE (existing) for emotion/threat, belief-dissonance for information-processing behavior. Dominant mechanism wins. — Math: dissonance = 1 - cos_similarity(belief_embedding, stimulus_embedding); behavior = argmax(dissonance → protect, ~dissonance → assimilate); [personality-psychology+Big-Five-FFM+dynamical-systems+Bayesian-precision-weighting] Big Five Trait Amplifier Layer — Personality as Precision Priors. The model ignores person.traits (neuroticism, openness, extraversion, conscientiousness, agreeableness) entirely. Traits are stable individual differences that modulate how any situation is processed — they are meta-priors on precision. Implement as a multiplicative layer applied before free-energy calculation: neuroticism scales threat-precision by (1 + 0.8*neuroticism); openness scales novelty-precision and reduces belief rigidity; extraversion scales social-need precision; conscientiousness scales fairness/rule-violation precision; agreeableness scales belonging-need precision. This differentiates individuals in the same situation (the introvert is socially drained, the extravert is energized). Maps directly to personality, psychopathology (high neuroticism → anxiety loop) and development benchmarks. — Math: precision_i = base_precision_i * prod_j(trait_weight_j(trait_j)); trait_weight maps each Big Five dimension to specific need precisions via a 5×8 interaction matrix",
